1. Palatium primum. The first Roman settlement on the Palatine was sometimes called Roma quadrata, ‘ square Rome,’ from the quadrilateral shape of the hill.

3. Geryone interempto. Geryon, a monster with three bodies and powerful wings, lived in Erytheia, a fabulous island in the western Mediterranean. The slaying of Geryon and the capture of his famous oxen formed one of the twelve labours of Hercules, who, on his return, passed through Gaul and Italy.
